<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7868900>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Metarhizium lymantriidae (BUM 818). A. The larva of noctuid infected by the related species, M. rileyi. B. The larva of tussock moth infected by M. lymantriidae. C. Colony on PDA medium, 16 days. D. Colony reverse. E, F. Phialides with conidia chain. G, H. Conidia. I. Hyphae and phialide with budding conidia. Scale bars: A–D = 1 cm, E–I = 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7868900/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

